
[1]solidity

   SOLID'ITY, n. [L. soliditas.]

   1. Firmness; hardness; density; compactness; that quality of bodies
   whcih resists impression and penetration; opposed to fluidity. That
   which hinders the apporach of two bodies moving ine towards another, I
   call solidity.

   2. Fullness of matter; opposed to hollowness.

   3. Moral firmness; soundness; strength; validity; truth; certainty; as
   opposed to weakness or fallaciounes; as the soildity of arguments or
   reasonig; the solidity of principles, truths or opinious.

   4. In geometry, the solid contents of a body.
